title: For Sale:  Remington 30-30 Accelerator ammo
postcontent: I have three boxes of Remington Accelerators in 30-30. These are essentially 55 grain .224 soft point bullets inside a plastic sabot. They are very high velocity, with a muzzle velocity of 3400 fps, from a 30-30! Remington first introduced these in 1977, but they haven't been available for many years. Remington was pressured by the FBI to discontinue these because the bullets don't touch the barrel's rifling so they don't get any distinguishable rifling marks on them when fired.These cartridges are RARE - you won't find ANY for sale on Armslist, Gunbroker or GunsAmerica. The last time I saw any of these for sale was at a gun show back in 2003, and they were $35 a box BACK THEN.Use them for varmint hunting or just plinking if you want, or add them to your ammo collection. Take one, two or all three boxes - they're $35 per box.
